This is the clean-source build output.  The previous "Window framebuffer support
not available" error was caused by SDL_RENDER=OFF in CMakeLists.txt, which
prevented SDL_GetWindowSurface from working on macOS Cocoa (the Cocoa video driver
has no software CreateWindowFramebuffer — it relies on the Metal texture
framebuffer path through the render API).  Enabling SDL_RENDER=ON auto-detects
SDL_RENDER_METAL=ON on Apple platforms, which is sufficient.
